This paper discusses the challenges and issues related to big medical data, which involves the intersection of computer science, engineering, and life sciences. The paper focuses on the unique characteristics of medical data, prioritized tasks in clinician research, algorithms and benchmarks for medical data, and the need for collaboration between different fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the intersection of computer science and other fields. Other likely sub-categories include cs.DB (Databases), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as these fields are relevant to the analysis and processing of big data.
